HEADWORD: Fragment
<hw>Frag"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fragmentum</ets>, fr. frangere to break: cf. F.
<ets>fragment</ets>. See <er>Break</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>A
part broken off; a small, detached portion; an imperfect part; <as>as, a
<ex>fragment</ex> of an ancient writing</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gather up the <qex>fragments</qex> that remain.</q> <rj><qau>John
vi. 12.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fragmental</ent>⟦br⟧
